attributes.magic: PE32 executable (GUI) Intel 80386, for MS Windows

threat_severity.level_description: Severity HIGH because it was considered ransomware. Other contributing factors were that it has known exploits and it could not be run in sandboxes.

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: This binary is a sophisticated information stealer or backdoor that utilizes extensive anti-analysis and data exfiltration techniques. It employs a custom dynamic API resolver (sub_40182a/sub_401ac3) to hide its reliance on sensitive Windows APIs. Key behaviors include: 1) Spyware capabilities: Logic in sub_404255 captures screen data, formats it into .BMP files, and prepares it for exfiltration. 2) C2 Communication: sub_4031ee implements an HTTP POST-based beaconing mechanism using custom Base64 encoding and encrypted data strings. 3) Reconnaissance: The malware performs deep system auditing, including OS version fingerprinting (sub_401f0f) and recursive file system searching (sub_4067ad). 4) Cryptography: Implementation of custom stream ciphers (likely Salsa20/ChaCha20 in sub_40209c and RC4-like logic in sub_4017aa) for string and network traffic obfuscation.
